metadata.name: Botanical Remains
metadata.description:
Amidst the ruins of time and decay, a wonder blooms, in its own special way. Flowers and leaves, in vibrant hues, sprout from the remnants of a world we once knew.

As nature reclaims what was left behind, The skeleton of a world now entwined with the flora that seeks to reclaim the earth, a poignant reminder of the cycle of birth.

For even in the face of death and decay, There is beauty to be found, in every way. In the remains of what was once alive, A new form of life begins to thrive.

This is the magic of botanical remains, A testament to the resilience of nature's reign. As we contemplate the beauty that still remains, we find solace in life's eternal refrain.

For even as we fade away, the earth continues, a constant display of the beauty that can emerge from pain, the cycle of life, in botanical remains.
